{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Spindle and kinetochore-associated protein 1 (SKA1, also known as SKA complex subunit 1) is a component of the SKA1 complex (consists of Ska1, Ska2, and Ska3/Rama1), a microtubule-binding subcomplex of the outer kinetochore that is essential for proper chromosome segregation [[cite:PUB00061771]]. It is required for timely anaphase onset during mitosis, when chromosomes undergo bipolar attachment on spindle microtubules leading to silencing of the spindle checkpoint [[cite:PUB00061805]]. The SKA1 complex is a direct component of the kinetochore-microtubule interface and directly associates with microtubules as oligomeric assemblies. The complex facilitates the processive movement of microspheres along a microtubule in a depolymerisation-coupled manner. SKA1 contains a microtubule-binding domain that interacts with tubulins using multiple contact sites that allow the Ska complex to bind microtubules in multiple modes [[cite:PUB00077600]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR042031", "name" "SKA1 microtubule binding domain superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR28573" "SPINDLE AND KINETOCHORE-ASSOCIATED PROTEIN 1"}, "pfam" {"PF07160" "Spindle and kinetochore-associated protein 1"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Spindle and kinetochore-associated protein 1", "short" "SKA1"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 4, "domain_architectures" 45, "proteomes" 1076, "taxa" 4323, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 2003, "sets" 0, "proteins" 1903, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 1234}, "pathways" 24}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR009829", :literature {"PUB00061771" {"URL" nil, "issue" "23", "authors" ["Hanisch A" "Sillje HH" "Nigg EA."], "ISO_journal" "EMBO J.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.